WEBVTT

00:09.900 --> 00:15.360
And now DreamWorks the
penguins of Madagascar.

00:15.360 --> 00:18.800
[MUSIC PENGUINS OF MADAGASCAR
THEME SONG]

00:51.190 --> 00:52.370
-Cute and cuddly boys.

01:06.560 --> 01:08.540
[HEAVY METAL MUSIC PLAYING]

01:08.540 --> 01:12.020
-(SINGING) Who is your baby?

01:12.020 --> 01:14.010
King Julien is your baby!

01:16.990 --> 01:20.470
Baby, baby, baby!

01:20.470 --> 01:22.960
Baby!

01:22.960 --> 01:28.720
-Gentlemen, if I'm known for
one thing, it's my patience

01:28.720 --> 01:29.670
-Actually, Skipper--

01:29.670 --> 01:30.730
-(ANGRILY) Patience!

01:30.730 --> 01:32.750
I'm known for my
saint-like patience.

01:32.750 --> 01:35.870
But this time, those ringtails
have pushed me too far.

01:35.870 --> 01:36.770
[HEAVY METAL MUSIC PLAYING]

01:36.770 --> 01:38.710
-Now, blow, big man.

01:38.710 --> 01:41.140
[HORN BLOWING]

01:41.140 --> 01:44.050
[DRUMS AND CYMBALS]

01:44.050 --> 01:46.490
-It's bad enough when
they listen to music--

01:46.490 --> 01:48.240
-But it's worse when
they make their own.

01:48.240 --> 01:52.500
-This calls for measures, the
drasticker, the better-er.

01:52.500 --> 01:54.390
KOWALSKI: And where should
I transfer the lemurs?

01:54.390 --> 01:56.370
SKIPPER: What's the
furthest point from us?

01:56.370 --> 01:57.620
-The petting zoo.

01:57.620 --> 01:58.530
-Yeah.

01:58.530 --> 02:02.460
All those tiny grabby hands, the
nose-pickers, the tail-tuggers.

02:02.460 --> 02:04.550
It's bratatorial combat!

02:04.550 --> 02:05.360
[DEVIOUS LAUGHING]

02:05.360 --> 02:06.440
The petting zoo!

02:06.440 --> 02:07.970
I like it!

02:07.970 --> 02:09.880
-Oh, who's going to
be our new neighbour?

02:09.880 --> 02:10.760
Can it be Roger?

02:10.760 --> 02:11.530
I like Roger.

02:11.530 --> 02:13.670
-Kowalski, I'm in a giving mood.

02:13.670 --> 02:14.540
grant the boy his wish.

02:14.540 --> 02:17.010
[DIALLING]

02:22.920 --> 02:27.080
[SIGHING]

02:27.080 --> 02:27.780
-Whoa!

02:27.780 --> 02:29.760
[LOUD THUMP]

02:29.760 --> 02:32.750
MAN (ON RADIO): Hey, yo,
Alice, I don't know about this.

02:32.750 --> 02:35.080
The computer says I'm supposed
to transfer the lemur to--

02:35.080 --> 02:37.560
-Are you questioning
the computer?

02:37.560 --> 02:40.040
The same computer that
spits out our paychecks?

02:40.040 --> 02:41.100
MAN (ON RADIO): Excellent point.

02:41.100 --> 02:42.010
[GROANING]

02:42.010 --> 02:42.880
-No!

02:42.880 --> 02:44.690
This is a mistaken thing.

02:44.690 --> 02:46.890
We should not be in this cage.

02:46.890 --> 02:49.020
Well, maybe Mort.

02:49.020 --> 02:49.720
-Hello?

02:49.720 --> 02:51.100
-Hello, Roger.

02:51.100 --> 02:52.560
Welcome to the neighbourhood.

02:52.560 --> 02:53.260
-Thank you, but I--

02:53.260 --> 02:55.090
-You'll find your
new home is outfitted

02:55.090 --> 02:57.910
with all the modern
conveniences, tiki bar,

02:57.910 --> 02:59.100
bouncy, throne.

02:59.100 --> 03:00.590
[CRASHING]

03:00.590 --> 03:02.080
[BOING]

03:02.080 --> 03:04.450
We can fix that, maybe.

03:04.450 --> 03:07.450
-Rico, warm this house
with a tasteful gift.

03:07.450 --> 03:08.630
[WRETCHING]

03:08.630 --> 03:10.130
-Hey, Roger.

03:10.130 --> 03:12.250
-Oh, very nice, very classy.

03:12.250 --> 03:12.950
Thank you.

03:12.950 --> 03:13.650
Thanks.

03:13.650 --> 03:15.030
Um, can I ask one thing?

03:15.030 --> 03:16.590
Doesn't someone else live here?

03:16.590 --> 03:18.460
-Not anymore.

03:18.460 --> 03:21.940
[MANIACAL LAUGHING]

03:21.940 --> 03:24.430
[WHIMPERING]

03:26.430 --> 03:28.550
-Everything in my
kingly kingdom,

03:28.550 --> 03:31.350
including my kingly
kingdom, is gone.

03:31.350 --> 03:32.800
-Yeah, but we got other things.

03:32.800 --> 03:33.500
-Yeah?

03:33.500 --> 03:34.240
Like what?

03:34.240 --> 03:36.060
MORT: I found a
cotton ball doggy.

03:36.060 --> 03:38.170
-Hey, quick question.

03:38.170 --> 03:39.410
Is this guy one of yours?

03:39.410 --> 03:41.620
-Mort, get off the sheep.

03:41.620 --> 03:42.660
-Thanks.

03:42.660 --> 03:43.710
I'm Randy.

03:43.710 --> 03:46.550
Welcome to the land
of a thousands hands.

03:46.550 --> 03:48.480
-Yeah, yeah you could
keep your welcomes, Randy,

03:48.480 --> 03:53.760
because (GRUNTING) I
will not be staying.

03:53.760 --> 03:55.660
[EXHAUSTED SIGHING]

03:55.660 --> 03:57.040
Maurice, I am bushed.

03:57.040 --> 03:58.620
You do the tunnelling
to freedom.

03:58.620 --> 03:59.320
-Why?

03:59.320 --> 04:00.860
I think it's kind of nice here.

04:00.860 --> 04:05.120
-Yes, but fortunately I am king,
so you don't have to think.

04:05.120 --> 04:06.140
You only have to do.

04:06.140 --> 04:09.250
And now what I, your king,
wants you to be doing

04:09.250 --> 04:10.870
is dig, dig, dig.

04:10.870 --> 04:11.720
[THUMP]

04:11.720 --> 04:12.480
[DIGGING]

04:12.480 --> 04:16.150
Eh, Maurice, why
are they doing what

04:16.150 --> 04:17.810
I'm telling you to be doing?

04:17.810 --> 04:20.070
-Because you're the king, right?

04:20.070 --> 04:20.980
-Obviously.

04:20.980 --> 04:22.520
With a tail like that?

04:22.520 --> 04:25.670
-Only a king could have
a tail so magnificent.

04:25.670 --> 04:27.050
ALL: Yay for the king!

04:27.050 --> 04:30.620
-I'm sorry, but King
Julien already has

04:30.620 --> 04:31.840
someone that blindly
follows him--

04:31.840 --> 04:32.540
[LOUD KICK]

04:32.540 --> 04:34.390
Whoa!

04:34.390 --> 04:35.400
-We're staying.

04:35.400 --> 04:36.390
ALL: Yay!

04:36.390 --> 04:38.720
-Ya here that, boys?

04:38.720 --> 04:41.110
That's the sweet sound
of lemur-free living.

04:41.110 --> 04:41.810
-Hee-Haw!

04:41.810 --> 04:42.790
[LOUD CRASH]

04:42.790 --> 04:44.760
-Ow.

04:44.760 --> 04:48.510
-(NERVOUSLY) Roger, are you OK?

04:48.510 --> 04:50.340
-Well, guys, no.

04:50.340 --> 04:51.740
No, I'm not.

04:51.740 --> 04:53.930
It's just this habitat.

04:53.930 --> 04:55.910
It simply doesn't have the
amount of swimmable water

04:55.910 --> 04:58.190
that a wide-bodied
boy like myself needs.

04:58.190 --> 04:59.960
-We've got plenty of
water in our pool.

04:59.960 --> 05:02.460
-Yeah, dip your skinnies any
time you want, neighbour.

05:02.460 --> 05:04.310
Our Habitat es su habitat.

05:08.130 --> 05:09.940
-Cannonball!

05:09.940 --> 05:10.640
[LOUD SPLASH]

05:10.640 --> 05:12.120
ALL: Ah!

05:12.120 --> 05:14.380
[LOUD SPLASH]

05:14.380 --> 05:15.080
[LOUD EXPLOSION]

05:15.080 --> 05:16.070
-Toxic gas!

05:16.070 --> 05:17.290
Evacuate!

05:17.290 --> 05:19.230
[METAL CLANKING]

05:19.230 --> 05:20.210
[COUGHING]

05:20.210 --> 05:21.180
-Stuck.

05:21.180 --> 05:22.640
PRIVATE: (ECHOING)
Let us out of here.

05:22.640 --> 05:23.330
[LOUD POUNDING]

05:23.330 --> 05:24.090
SKIPPER: Open up now!

05:24.090 --> 05:24.790
[HUMMING]

05:24.790 --> 05:26.040
That's an order!

05:26.040 --> 05:27.010
[HUMMING]

05:27.010 --> 05:28.210
[LOW MUSIC PLAYING]

05:28.210 --> 05:29.990
[HUMMING]

05:29.990 --> 05:31.450
-(DISAPPOINTINGLY) Oh, no fish.

05:31.450 --> 05:32.930
-I don't understand it.

05:32.930 --> 05:34.450
What happened to our lunch?

05:34.450 --> 05:35.320
-Guys, you're the best.

05:35.320 --> 05:36.330
You're the best.

05:36.330 --> 05:37.510
Leaving that bowl
of fish for me.

05:37.510 --> 05:38.780
You're the best.

05:38.780 --> 05:39.480
What was that anyway?

05:39.480 --> 05:40.800
Was that mackerel?

05:40.800 --> 05:42.830
KOWALSKI: This presentation
on Dr. Blowhole's lair

05:42.830 --> 05:46.460
is classified, triple top
secret for your eyes only and--

05:46.460 --> 05:47.390
[LOUD CRASHING AND SMASHING]

05:47.390 --> 05:48.090
-Guys, guys!

05:52.210 --> 05:53.310
Sorry about that.

05:53.310 --> 05:54.560
[GRUNTING]

05:54.560 --> 05:55.370
-No problem.

05:55.370 --> 05:58.990
I just spent three
painstaking weeks building it.

05:58.990 --> 05:59.690
-Listen.

05:59.690 --> 06:02.550
I'm working on an original
musical, Gator in the park, OK,

06:02.550 --> 06:04.780
and I'm not sure
which lyric is better.

06:04.780 --> 06:06.890
I have lots of teeth
at the end of my snout

06:06.890 --> 06:09.860
or if you call me cruel
names I'm likely to pout.

06:09.860 --> 06:11.570
Ooh, now that I
say it out loud it

06:11.570 --> 06:12.770
should definitely
be the second one.

06:12.770 --> 06:14.640
OK, thanks, guys.

06:14.640 --> 06:16.910
-Men, I'm beginning to
see a flaw in this plan.

06:23.830 --> 06:26.680
-Why do they get to
touch the royal feet?

06:26.680 --> 06:30.020
-Because Mort, they
have soft, furry paws.

06:30.020 --> 06:33.530
-But I have soft furry paws too.

06:33.530 --> 06:37.230
-Yes, but they are
also cute and adorable.

06:37.230 --> 06:40.140
-But I am cute and adorable too.

06:40.140 --> 06:43.450
-Hmm, yeah, I'm just going
to bottom line this for you.

06:43.450 --> 06:45.000
They're not you.

06:45.000 --> 06:46.720
-(ANGRILY) Stupid bunnies.

06:46.720 --> 06:48.190
-Good news, lemurs.

06:48.190 --> 06:49.360
You're going back home.

06:49.360 --> 06:50.530
-Hooray!

06:50.530 --> 06:54.160
-Eh, maybe you
penguins are confused.

06:54.160 --> 06:55.310
We are home.

06:55.310 --> 06:56.350
-What, this?

06:56.350 --> 06:57.740
This isn't your home.

06:57.740 --> 06:59.920
-You belong in a
habitat customised

06:59.920 --> 07:02.180
to your specific lemurish needs.

07:02.180 --> 07:05.760
-Uh, no, this petting
zoo is much better.

07:05.760 --> 07:08.570
Look, I've got
way more subjects.

07:08.570 --> 07:10.100
-Ooh, bunnies.

07:12.700 --> 07:15.990
-And they do everything he
wants, so I don't have to.

07:15.990 --> 07:17.620
-Yes, when I say hop--

07:17.620 --> 07:19.790
-They say how high?

07:19.790 --> 07:21.270
-Uh, no, they just hop.

07:21.270 --> 07:22.870
Maximum height is a given.

07:22.870 --> 07:24.000
Hop, Fluffy.

07:24.000 --> 07:29.520
[JET ENGINE NOISE]

07:29.520 --> 07:30.220
See?

07:30.220 --> 07:31.840
Mad hops.

07:31.840 --> 07:36.330
So to be honest we really miss
the old kingdom not so much.

07:36.330 --> 07:37.510
-I do.

07:37.510 --> 07:38.870
-Forget it.

07:38.870 --> 07:40.760
We didn't need their
permission before.

07:40.760 --> 07:41.580
We don't need it now.

07:46.110 --> 07:47.370
-Permission?

07:47.370 --> 07:49.000
Before?

07:49.000 --> 07:53.420
-Fellas, it's time to undo
this neighbour swap fiasco.

07:53.420 --> 07:55.420
-Just a few keystrokes--

07:55.420 --> 07:56.580
-Uh-uh.

07:56.580 --> 08:00.280
I was expecting this kind of
sneaky Peter tricking from you

08:00.280 --> 08:00.980
penguins.

08:00.980 --> 08:03.790
Touch that computing
thingy and face

08:03.790 --> 08:07.390
the wrath of my newest subjects.

08:07.390 --> 08:08.810
-What, the cute bunnies?

08:08.810 --> 08:12.860
-If I am telling them to open
up a can of whoop penguin,

08:12.860 --> 08:14.510
then this can will be opened.

08:14.510 --> 08:15.210
[ALL LAUGHING]

08:15.210 --> 08:15.980
Believe you me.

08:15.980 --> 08:17.430
-You can't be serious.

08:17.430 --> 08:19.400
You want us to be
afraid of fluffy?

08:19.400 --> 08:20.750
Ooh!

08:20.750 --> 08:21.450
ALL: Whoa!

08:26.870 --> 08:29.090
[WHIMPERING]

08:31.840 --> 08:32.540
-Eh!

08:32.540 --> 08:33.240
-Ah!

08:36.490 --> 08:38.950
[BOUNCING]

08:41.420 --> 08:43.220
[WHIMPERING]

08:45.670 --> 08:48.430
-Wow, I was totally
bluffing back there.

08:48.430 --> 08:52.810
I had no idea you really had
such sick booty kicking skills.

08:52.810 --> 08:53.510
[LAUGHING]

08:53.510 --> 08:54.790
-Tell you what.

08:54.790 --> 08:57.100
Baby carrots for
everyone, that's what.

08:57.100 --> 08:59.370
ALL: Yay for carrots!

08:59.370 --> 09:00.530
-Punches.

09:00.530 --> 09:02.730
They were so cottony.

09:02.730 --> 09:08.610
-It was like a macabre ballet
of adorability and pain.

09:08.610 --> 09:11.190
-On the bright side,
at least we don't

09:11.190 --> 09:12.780
have Julien singing anymore.

09:12.780 --> 09:15.450
ROGER: (SINGING) Would
love a gator like me!

09:15.450 --> 09:16.480
Oh, oh boy.

09:16.480 --> 09:17.200
I hit a clam.

09:17.200 --> 09:17.890
Hold on.

09:17.890 --> 09:21.170
(SINGING HIGH PITCHED
CRACKING TONE) Me, me, me.

09:21.170 --> 09:22.650
[GRUNTING]

09:22.650 --> 09:25.120
[SCREAMING]

09:25.120 --> 09:26.360
-What up, birds?

09:26.360 --> 09:28.380
-We're looking for
weakness in the enemy.

09:28.380 --> 09:29.840
-The little tyrant, huh?

09:29.840 --> 09:33.220
Yeah, last night he told me to
surrender my puffy wooliness

09:33.220 --> 09:34.200
unto him.

09:34.200 --> 09:36.000
Just about surrendered
my hoof unto his--

09:36.000 --> 09:38.260
-Then our goals are the same.

09:38.260 --> 09:40.190
The only question is the means.

09:40.190 --> 09:43.820
-Hey, you remember how I got
kicked out of here, don't you?

09:43.820 --> 09:47.190
-Yeah, you did a fairly
white puncture job on a kid.

09:47.190 --> 09:50.120
-I don't think we'll ever get
Julien to bite a zoo visitor.

09:50.120 --> 09:53.270
-Well, who says
it has to be him?

09:53.270 --> 09:54.240
[FLAPPING LIPS]

09:54.240 --> 09:58.620
-Randy, underneath that sweater
beats a heart of a wolf.

09:58.620 --> 10:01.480
-I bite the people
and then we go home?

10:01.480 --> 10:03.630
-Just a nibble,
no skin breakage.

10:03.630 --> 10:05.830
-And stupid bunnies stay here?

10:05.830 --> 10:07.040
-Exactly.

10:07.040 --> 10:10.650
-(EXCITEDLY) I'm gonna
bite the peoples!

10:10.650 --> 10:12.770
-I want two choco
bombs, five gum

10:12.770 --> 10:14.740
breakers, and a
large slurp soda.

10:14.740 --> 10:16.230
-Ooh, and zippy sticks.

10:16.230 --> 10:17.430
-10 zippy sticks.

10:17.430 --> 10:18.220
-Skipper?

10:18.220 --> 10:20.070
The Vesuvius twins
are sugaring up,

10:20.070 --> 10:22.080
then they'll be en route
to the petting zoo.

10:22.080 --> 10:23.930
-10-4 Kowalski.

10:23.930 --> 10:25.900
The Vesuvius twins, perfect.

10:25.900 --> 10:27.940
If anyone deserves
Mort's mighty bite,

10:27.940 --> 10:29.580
it's Park Avenue's brattiest.

10:29.580 --> 10:30.380
[MORT CHOMPING]

10:30.380 --> 10:31.350
[LOUD THUD]

10:31.350 --> 10:32.800
-Ow, I'm stuck!

10:32.800 --> 10:34.260
-Get him off of there.

10:34.260 --> 10:35.710
We need those chompers.

10:35.710 --> 10:37.140
-(EXCITEDLY) All right, animals.

10:37.140 --> 10:38.600
-For petting.

10:38.600 --> 10:39.660
-Pull!

10:39.660 --> 10:41.190
The biting window is closing.

10:41.190 --> 10:42.450
[WRETCHING]

10:42.450 --> 10:43.250
[GROANING]

10:43.250 --> 10:45.090
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

10:45.090 --> 10:47.150
-Find your happy place.

10:47.150 --> 10:48.570
[GRUNTING]

10:48.570 --> 10:49.980
[GROANING]

10:49.980 --> 10:51.780
-Ooh, look at those.

10:51.780 --> 10:53.000
-Monkey things.

10:53.000 --> 10:54.650
-Ooh, fresh meat.

10:54.650 --> 10:56.060
(FRIGHTENDLY) I've
changed my mind.

10:56.060 --> 10:57.900
I don't like the
petting zoo anymore.

10:57.900 --> 10:59.560
We'll protect you, Your Majesty.

10:59.560 --> 11:01.670
-Puh-ha-ha, from what?

11:01.670 --> 11:04.260
These humans are obviously
bringing tributes

11:04.260 --> 11:07.300
of tasty snacks to
the petting zoo king.

11:07.300 --> 11:09.100
I accept your offerings.

11:09.100 --> 11:09.800
-(FRANTICALLY) Ah!

11:09.800 --> 11:12.300
This thing is attacking me!

11:12.300 --> 11:13.300
-Get it off!

11:13.300 --> 11:14.710
Get off!

11:14.710 --> 11:16.070
[SLURPING]

11:16.070 --> 11:17.720
-Oh, brain freeze.

11:17.720 --> 11:20.320
-No, no Mrs. Vesuvius,
lemurs shouldn't even

11:20.320 --> 11:21.470
be in the petting zoo.

11:21.470 --> 11:23.480
Frankly, I don't even
know how they got there

11:23.480 --> 11:25.890
in the first place,
stupid computer.

11:25.890 --> 11:27.870
-Mission accomplished, boys.

11:27.870 --> 11:28.860
MORT: Hooray!

11:28.860 --> 11:30.360
[RATTLING]

11:30.360 --> 11:31.150
-No!

11:31.150 --> 11:32.970
I do not want this kingdom!

11:32.970 --> 11:35.000
Take me back to my
petting kingdom.

11:35.000 --> 11:37.220
I order you. (WHINING) Please.

11:37.220 --> 11:38.930
-Aw, guys.

11:38.930 --> 11:41.140
I'll sure miss our next
door neighbourliness.

11:41.140 --> 11:43.360
-Right, not going
to be the same.

11:43.360 --> 11:46.870
-Still, I can drop by
anytime, go for a swim,

11:46.870 --> 11:48.230
sing some show tunes.

11:48.230 --> 11:50.430
-Oh, uh--

11:50.430 --> 11:51.420
-Oh, yeah, yeah, great.

11:51.420 --> 11:52.380
Just-- just call first.

11:52.380 --> 11:53.590
-But I don't have a phone.

11:53.590 --> 11:54.910
-Oh, neither do we.

11:54.910 --> 11:55.610
Later!

11:59.100 --> 12:01.600
[MUSIC PLAYING]

12:11.580 --> 12:14.480
-Now that's a fine
looking poop deck.

12:14.480 --> 12:16.900
I mean, usually I trouble
with my poop deck.

12:16.900 --> 12:17.720
But this poop deck--

12:17.720 --> 12:20.560
[LAUGHTER]

12:22.500 --> 12:23.950
-Oh.

12:23.950 --> 12:27.940
-Rico, pass me the
final hull section.

12:27.940 --> 12:29.210
-Uh.
-(ANXIOUSLY) Come on, come on!

12:29.210 --> 12:29.910
Last piece!

12:29.910 --> 12:31.490
Let's cork this vessel.

12:31.490 --> 12:33.290
-I got nothin'.

12:33.290 --> 12:35.240
-Last piece missing.

12:35.240 --> 12:36.050
[LOUD THUMP]

12:36.050 --> 12:38.270
Weeks of work wasted.

12:38.270 --> 12:39.570
[FRUSTRATED GRUNTING]

12:39.570 --> 12:41.610
[LOUD THUMP]

12:41.610 --> 12:42.320
-Skipper.

12:42.320 --> 12:44.410
-Kowalski, cover
the Private's ears.

12:44.410 --> 12:47.330
I intend to use by angry words.

12:47.330 --> 12:49.750
[MUMBLED ANGRY YELLING]

12:53.630 --> 12:54.590
-Wow.

12:54.590 --> 12:56.430
-(SADLY) I still heard.

12:56.430 --> 12:59.360
-Yes, we can give you the
manufacturer's address,

12:59.360 --> 13:00.880
just not sure why you need it.

13:00.880 --> 13:03.540
-Primate, this is a
payback operation,

13:03.540 --> 13:05.070
missing piece payback.

13:05.070 --> 13:07.460
The less you know, the better.

13:07.460 --> 13:10.630
-Phil insists there
are no missing pieces.

13:10.630 --> 13:13.660
Apparently, your model
is the SS Fiskelukt.

13:13.660 --> 13:14.850
-(ANGRILY) Denmark!

13:14.850 --> 13:16.510
-Actually, Norway.

13:16.510 --> 13:18.250
-You don't have a problem
with the Norwegians,

13:18.250 --> 13:18.950
do you, Skipper?

13:18.950 --> 13:21.450
-No, I'm ambivalent
towards those fjord loving

13:21.450 --> 13:22.750
sons of Vikings.

13:22.750 --> 13:24.650
-They did event
the cheese slicer.

13:24.650 --> 13:26.390
(SARCASTICALLY) Well,
point for Norway.

13:26.390 --> 13:30.130
-100 years ago the Fiskelukt
sank in the New York bay

13:30.130 --> 13:33.590
with a full catch of
brine-preserved herring.

13:33.590 --> 13:37.870
-A full catch of tender
mouth watering herring?

13:37.870 --> 13:39.230
-Fish.

13:39.230 --> 13:42.330
-Your missing piece
represents the breach

13:42.330 --> 13:44.010
that sank the mighty vessel.

13:44.010 --> 13:48.410
A solemn reminder
of man's fragile--

13:48.410 --> 13:51.990
-And you're still thinking
about the herring, aren't you?

13:51.990 --> 13:54.490
-An entire sunken
fishing vessel.

13:54.490 --> 13:56.300
-Ripe for undersea retrieval.

13:56.300 --> 13:57.470
[BABBLING]

13:57.470 --> 14:00.160
-Ripe, is indeed
the word, Skipper.

14:00.160 --> 14:02.230
After 100 years of
ageing in brine,

14:02.230 --> 14:04.520
that herring should taste
somewhere between nectar

14:04.520 --> 14:07.270
of the gods and slap
your mama delicious!

14:07.270 --> 14:09.610
[EXCITED BABBLING]

14:10.590 --> 14:12.560
[CLANKING]

14:12.560 --> 14:13.820
[BABBLING]

14:17.700 --> 14:19.980
-Dial down the psycho, compadre.

14:19.980 --> 14:22.460
There's a time and a place
for that kind of madness.

14:22.460 --> 14:23.160
-Really?

14:23.160 --> 14:24.050
When is--

14:24.050 --> 14:27.260
-18 minutes from now, in
the lower New York Bay.

14:27.260 --> 14:30.250
[BOAT HORN BLARING]

14:36.240 --> 14:38.540
-Curse these Norwegian charts!

14:38.540 --> 14:41.390
I mean who measures in
metric beard lengths?

14:41.390 --> 14:42.640
-Nothing on sonar, Skipper.

14:42.640 --> 14:43.810
-Steady!

14:43.810 --> 14:46.520
Just get us within five
clicks of that wreck.

14:46.520 --> 14:49.540
Rico's uncanny fish sense
should kick in any--

14:49.540 --> 14:50.960
[SNIFFING]

14:50.960 --> 14:52.870
-Whoo!

14:52.870 --> 14:54.780
[EXCITED BABBLING]

14:54.780 --> 14:55.720
-Fish!

14:55.720 --> 14:58.030
-Mr. Kowalski, hard to port!

14:58.030 --> 15:01.070
Follow that beak!

15:01.070 --> 15:03.040
RICO: Fish!

15:03.040 --> 15:04.510
[SNIFFING]

15:04.510 --> 15:06.480
[BABBLING]

15:08.940 --> 15:11.400
[EXCITED BABBLING]

15:15.340 --> 15:17.120
SKIPPER: There she lies.

15:19.770 --> 15:22.160
Kowalski, herring
savage options.

15:22.160 --> 15:23.870
-Touchy operation, Skipper.

15:23.870 --> 15:25.950
After a century of
salt water that crate

15:25.950 --> 15:28.320
could fall apart with
the slightest jarring.

15:28.320 --> 15:30.960
The key words here
are slow, deliberate--

15:30.960 --> 15:31.660
-Whoo!

15:31.660 --> 15:32.640
-(PANICKING) Oh bad Rico!

15:32.640 --> 15:33.340
Bad Rico!

15:33.340 --> 15:36.080
SUBMARINE COMPUTER
VOICE: Torpedo one.

15:36.080 --> 15:38.040
SKIPPER: Sweet Chester Nibbits!

15:38.040 --> 15:40.020
[EXCITED BABBLING]

15:40.020 --> 15:41.140
-(DISAPPOINTINGLY) Oh man.

15:51.600 --> 15:52.590
KOWALSKI: Steady, steady.

15:56.130 --> 15:56.830
His fault.

15:56.830 --> 15:57.760
-Wow!

15:57.760 --> 15:58.460
[EXCITED BABBLING]

15:58.460 --> 15:59.850
-Whoa, whoa, whoa, Rico.

15:59.850 --> 16:02.100
This is what I'm
talking about, soldier.

16:02.100 --> 16:05.370
There's plenty of fish to go
around as long as everyone

16:05.370 --> 16:08.290
shows a little self discipline.

16:08.290 --> 16:09.630
[CHOMPING]

16:09.630 --> 16:13.090
-Skipper, you have got
to try this herring.

16:13.090 --> 16:14.170
-Don't mind if I do.

16:20.580 --> 16:23.030
[LOUD CHEWING]

16:28.020 --> 16:29.980
[DISSATISFIED GROANING]

16:29.980 --> 16:32.930
[ANGRY BABBLING]

16:32.930 --> 16:35.380
[ANGRY BABBLING]

16:40.290 --> 16:42.420
-(HAPPILY) Ha-ha-ha!

16:42.420 --> 16:43.120
What?

16:43.120 --> 16:44.390
[GULP]

16:44.390 --> 16:46.800
-(SWALLOWING) Mm, satisfying.

16:46.800 --> 16:49.520
-See, Rico, plenty to go around.

16:49.520 --> 16:50.500
Everybody good?
You good?

16:50.500 --> 16:51.520
You good?
You good?

16:51.520 --> 16:52.220
Great!

16:52.220 --> 16:53.420
Outstanding.

16:53.420 --> 16:56.260
[WHIMPERING]

16:56.260 --> 16:59.360
-Gentleman, send your
taste buds into retirement.

16:59.360 --> 17:01.240
There will never
be another flavour

17:01.240 --> 17:05.000
extravaganza like
that in our lifetime.

17:05.000 --> 17:06.700
[LOUD CLANKING]

17:06.700 --> 17:10.750
-That herring was so good it's
making me crave even more fish.

17:10.750 --> 17:11.680
[LAUGHING]

17:11.680 --> 17:15.890
[HYSTERICAL LAUGHING]
Seriously, though, good fish.

17:15.890 --> 17:17.070
[ANGRILY MUTTERING]

17:20.850 --> 17:22.160
-Still hungry, Rico?

17:22.160 --> 17:24.630
I don't know how you could
eat ordinary sardines

17:24.630 --> 17:26.710
after all that
delicious herring.

17:26.710 --> 17:28.610
[LOUD BURP]

17:28.610 --> 17:29.800
-Sardines?

17:29.800 --> 17:30.490
Fish!

17:35.350 --> 17:36.780
-Explain yourself, soldier.

17:36.780 --> 17:37.480
Fish!

17:37.480 --> 17:38.610
[INSANELY BABBLING]

17:38.610 --> 17:42.480
Kowalski, analysis.

17:42.480 --> 17:45.460
-Crazy eyes, babbling tongue--

17:45.460 --> 17:46.590
-Fish!

17:46.590 --> 17:47.880
-Uh-uh

17:47.880 --> 17:48.970
-Egad!

17:48.970 --> 17:52.100
I believe our Norwegian
herring was a bit too aged.

17:52.100 --> 17:54.190
-Never ever blame
the fish, Kowalski!

17:54.190 --> 17:55.470
-But don't you see?

17:55.470 --> 17:58.740
Private's contracted
bacterial Pisces dementia!

17:58.740 --> 18:01.760
A rare brain disease that's
turning him into a fish craving

18:01.760 --> 18:03.080
psychopath!

18:03.080 --> 18:03.780
-Hey!

18:03.780 --> 18:04.770
That's my thing!

18:04.770 --> 18:06.940
-Yeah, we don't
need two of those.

18:06.940 --> 18:08.050
Can it be cured?

18:08.050 --> 18:10.320
-It should wear off
in 24 hours as long

18:10.320 --> 18:11.840
as he doesn't feed the disease.

18:11.840 --> 18:14.880
That means no more
fish of any kind.

18:14.880 --> 18:17.190
If Private ingests so
much as a single sardine,

18:17.190 --> 18:19.460
he'll be like this forever.

18:19.460 --> 18:21.630
-Fish!

18:21.630 --> 18:23.230
Fish!

18:23.230 --> 18:24.200
Fish!

18:24.200 --> 18:25.510
Fish!

18:25.510 --> 18:26.210
Fish!

18:26.210 --> 18:27.950
SKIPPER: Stop that!

18:27.950 --> 18:29.770
-Well, on the bright
side, maybe this

18:29.770 --> 18:31.820
will teach Private
not to over indulge

18:31.820 --> 18:33.700
in so much brined herring.

18:33.700 --> 18:34.710
[CHUCKLING]

18:34.710 --> 18:37.600
-Hey, didn't you eat
as much as he did?

18:37.600 --> 18:40.920
-Why, yes I dooby-dooby-did!

18:40.920 --> 18:43.890
Fish!

18:43.890 --> 18:46.540
-Looks like we're on
psycho patrol, amigo.

18:46.540 --> 18:50.480
No fish for these two
for the next 24 hours.

18:50.480 --> 18:51.950
-Uh, what about you?

18:51.950 --> 18:54.150
-Luckily, my iron
constitution seems

18:54.150 --> 18:56.720
to have made me immune
to this Pisces dementia.

18:56.720 --> 18:58.890
[INSANE BABBLING]

18:58.890 --> 19:00.990
-Seriously.

19:00.990 --> 19:03.310
No effect.

19:03.310 --> 19:06.510
iron-clad constitution.

19:06.510 --> 19:08.250
[INSANE GROANING]

19:08.250 --> 19:09.980
Fish!

19:09.980 --> 19:12.460
[SCREAMING]

19:12.460 --> 19:13.940
[INSANE BABBLING]

19:13.940 --> 19:14.930
-Uh-uh-uh!

19:14.930 --> 19:16.420
No fish!

19:16.420 --> 19:18.520
ALICE: Feeding time!

19:18.520 --> 19:20.990
ALL: Fish!

19:20.990 --> 19:23.470
[INSANE BABBLING]

19:23.470 --> 19:25.160
Eat up, you disgusting animals!

19:25.160 --> 19:27.330
[GULPING]

19:27.330 --> 19:28.710
ALL: Ah!

19:28.710 --> 19:29.410
-Fish!

19:29.410 --> 19:30.820
[GULPING]

19:34.510 --> 19:37.830
-Since when do we
get four Ricos?

19:37.830 --> 19:39.440
-Wait, what?

19:39.440 --> 19:43.740
How come did nobody tell me
it was impersonation Tuesday?

19:43.740 --> 19:44.880
I call I get to be Maurice!

19:44.880 --> 19:45.580
[EXCITED LAUGHTER]

19:45.580 --> 19:48.550
[CLEARS THROAT] (IMITATING
MAURICE) Eh, hey, everybody.

19:48.550 --> 19:52.150
Stop having fun
because I am boring.

19:52.150 --> 19:52.850
Heh.

19:52.850 --> 19:54.010
And you should be boring too.

19:54.010 --> 19:54.710
Heh-heh.

19:54.710 --> 19:57.050
-I do not talk like that.

19:57.050 --> 19:58.360
(ROBOTIC TONE) Yes, you do.

19:58.360 --> 20:00.280
-Now that's just
your robot voice.

20:00.280 --> 20:01.670
-(ROBOTIC TONE)
End transmission.

20:01.670 --> 20:07.110
-And I'll be the King Julien,
which means-- the feet!

20:11.020 --> 20:11.720
-Hey!

20:11.720 --> 20:13.300
Baren von Greedenstein!

20:13.300 --> 20:15.390
Save some for the
rest of the flock!

20:15.390 --> 20:16.080
Gimme, gimme!

20:16.080 --> 20:18.050
Mine, mine, mine!

20:18.050 --> 20:20.020
[BABBLING]

20:21.500 --> 20:22.480
-Ooh!

20:22.480 --> 20:25.430
-Ooh, kabobs!

20:25.430 --> 20:26.910
[PAINFUL CRYING]

20:26.910 --> 20:28.380
[WHISTLING]

20:28.380 --> 20:29.080
-Great!

20:29.080 --> 20:30.050
All full then?

20:30.050 --> 20:31.980
[INSANE BABBLING]

20:31.980 --> 20:33.950
Whatever, freaks.

20:33.950 --> 20:34.770
-Uh-uh.

20:34.770 --> 20:35.810
No fish!

20:35.810 --> 20:38.170
MAN: Yo, zookeeper
lady, where you

20:38.170 --> 20:40.280
want this truckload
of fresh cod fillets?

20:40.280 --> 20:42.000
-Aw, no!

20:42.000 --> 20:42.700
ALL: Fish!

20:46.090 --> 20:47.060
Fish!

20:47.060 --> 20:48.580
[INSANE BABBLING]

20:49.900 --> 20:51.220
-This ain't happening!

20:51.220 --> 20:52.410
This ain't happening!

20:52.410 --> 20:54.890
[CAR TIRES SCREACHING]

21:05.600 --> 21:06.300
-Fish!

21:14.670 --> 21:16.590
-Pull the car over!

21:16.590 --> 21:17.290
-Ahh!

21:21.170 --> 21:21.920
[POLICE SIREN BLARING]

21:21.920 --> 21:22.620
Whoa!

21:29.860 --> 21:32.960
-Ah, fish.

21:32.960 --> 21:33.970
MAN: All right, people.

21:33.970 --> 21:36.000
That tuna ain't
gonna can itself.

21:36.000 --> 21:39.480
[MACHINE BEEPING]

21:39.480 --> 21:42.600
-Are you kidding me?

21:42.600 --> 21:44.130
[INSANE BABBLING]

21:44.130 --> 21:44.830
No!

21:48.380 --> 21:49.340
(OPERA VOICE SINGING) Feeesh!

21:55.350 --> 21:56.810
[HAPPILY LAUGHING]

21:56.810 --> 21:58.370
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
yeah, you go ahead.

21:58.370 --> 21:59.790
Suckers.

21:59.790 --> 22:02.010
[CHOMPING]

22:11.390 --> 22:13.870
[CHOMPING]

22:21.530 --> 22:25.380
-Rico, why is my mouth crunchy?

22:25.380 --> 22:28.650
[HAPPILY LAUGHING]

22:28.650 --> 22:29.350
[CRASH]

22:29.350 --> 22:31.830
[CAR ALARM BLARING]

22:33.320 --> 22:38.270
And so, for conspicuous
bravery in the face of uh,

22:38.270 --> 22:42.650
himself uh, times three,
I hereby award Rico

22:42.650 --> 22:44.810
this ceremonial
smoked Alaskan salmon.

22:44.810 --> 22:46.280
-Ah, fish!

22:46.280 --> 22:48.110
-I think we all
learned something

22:48.110 --> 22:50.210
today about
unrestrained gluttony.

22:50.210 --> 22:53.170
-Gimmie, gimmie, gimmie,
mine, mine, mine!

22:53.170 --> 22:56.130
[GOBBLING]

22:56.130 --> 22:57.530
-It's Rico's thing.

22:57.530 --> 22:58.730
[RICO BABBLING]

22:58.730 --> 23:01.780
[MUSIC PENGUINS OF MADAGASCAR
THEME SONG]
